Following a temporary downtime in the check-in system of Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos, the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) hereby appeal to airlines and passengers for patience and understanding. According to Henrietta Yakubu (Mrs.), General Manager, Corporate Affairs  of the authority saying FAAN has already mobilized necessary resources to address the challenge, and all hands are presently on deck to restore normalcy in passenger facilitation. To avoid flight delays, the Authority will like to advise passengers to leave their homes early, so as to complete all check-in formalities in good time. FAAN….. Committed to her core values of Safety, Security and Comfort.